# Contact form delivery (Web3Forms).
#
# Get a key: go to https://web3forms.com, enter the inbox that should receive
# messages, and they email you an access key. No account needed.
#
# Then:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env` and paste the key below (local development).
#   2. Add the same variable in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard under
#      Settings -> Environment variables (production).
#
# Without it the contact form is replaced by a visible email address, so the
# page still works — it just can't take messages.
#
# This key is safe to expose: it only permits posting to the inbox it was
# issued for, which is why it carries the PUBLIC_ prefix.
PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY=
